{
  "title": "ISic001660. Lilybaeum honours Diognetos Megas as euergetes",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\">ὁ</span>  <span data-text=\"δᾶμος\">δᾶμος</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"τῶν\">τῶν</span> Λιλυβαιιτᾶν <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διόγνητον\n                    Δαματρίου Μήγαν\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόγνητον\">Διόγνητον</span>  <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Δαματρίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Δαματρίου\">Δαματρίου</span></span>  <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"secondName\" data-text=\"Μήγαν\">Μήγα[ν]</span></span>  <br id=\"al5-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-text=\"εὐεργέταν\">ε̣ὐ̣ε̣ρ̣γ̣έ̣τ̣α̣ν̣</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Andoni Llamazares</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"ὁ\">Ο</span><span data-text=\"δᾶμος\">ΔΑΜΟΣ</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"τῶν\">ΤΩΝ</span>ΛΙΛΥΒΑΙΙΤΑΝ<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Διόγνητον\n                    Δαματρίου Μήγαν\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Διόγνητον\">ΔΙΟΓΝΗΤΟΝ</span><br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Δαματρίου\"><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"patronym\" data-text=\"Δαματρίου\">ΔΑΜΑΤΡΙΟΥ</span></span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"secondName\" data-text=\"Μήγαν\">ΜΗΓΑ[.]</span></span><br id=\"al5-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">5</span><span data-text=\"εὐεργέταν\">.........</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>text checked against photograph</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>The people of the Lilybaitani honour Diognetos Megas, son of Damatrios as benefactor</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>This man is the father of one Marcus Valerius Chorton, honours for whom are recorded in two lost inscriptions (one from Mazara, one from Marsala), preserved in the antiquarian tradition (<a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001096\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001096</a> = IG XIV.273) and <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001097\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001097</a> = IG XIV.277). The inscription is a rare (for Sicily) attestation of an individual honoured as euergetes (benefactor).</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 34.0951 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> 1965.0507 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001282</a></li><li> Manni Piraino 1963 159-162 no.2 tav.52 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001782\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001782</a></li><li> Manni Piraino 1984 125-126 no. 155 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002035\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002035</a></li><li> Wilson 1990 361 n.107 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001509</a></li><li> Di Stefano 2006 547 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001365\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001365</a></li><li> Brugnone 2021 63 fig. 7 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002691\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002691</a></li><li> Brugnone 2024 469 fig.473 </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"><p>Regular and neat letters, thinly incised, all of equal height, and slightly variable width, without serifs. Alpha with broken bar, beta with closed loops (upper slightly smaller), Mu has full length slanting strokes; omicron full size; sigma has horizontal top and bottom, middle strokes taking the full width; rhomboid omega.</p> Line 1-5  25  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
  "divs": [
